      • initialize

        public static boolean initialize(Context context,
                 java.lang.String accountName,
                 java.lang.String profileName,
                 java.lang.String environmentName,
                 int options)
        Initializer for the Tealium Library.

        This must be called before any other method calls.

        Parameters:
        context - - any available context.
        accountName - - your profile account name.
        profileName - - this application's profile name
        environmentName - - "dev", "qa", or "prod"
        options - - 0 for default, Tealium.OPT_* for different options.
        Returns:
        if the library was initialized with no complications. See LogCat for details otherwise.

      • trackItemClicked

        @Deprecated
public static void trackItemClicked(java.lang.String itemName,
                               java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> variables)
        Deprecated. 
        This method is deprecated, use Tealium.track(Object,Map,String) instead. This call is similar to trackItemClicked(String) except it allows any custom variables to be passed. NOTE: the variables parameter will be utilized to override those passed into the constructor or the setVariables() method.
        Parameters:
        itemName - the name of the item to be tracked. This is similar to a 'link' being tracked by traditional web analytics
        variables - any set of name/value pairs that need to be passed to the utag platform.

      • trackScreenViewed

        @Deprecated
public static void trackScreenViewed(java.lang.String viewName)
        Deprecated. 
        This method is deprecated, use Tealium.track(Object,Map,String) instead. This method can be used to track the display of sub-screens within a single activity, such as tab content or a dialog. NOTE: do NOT call this method to track the display of the Activity itself, as this is already performed by the lifecycle methods automatically.
        Parameters:
        viewName - the name of the screen. This is similar to a 'page' in traditional web analytics

      • track

        public static boolean track(java.lang.Object activtyViewOrThrowable,
            java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> optionalData,
            java.lang.String eventName)
        Manual track call. Usage:
        Parameters:
        activtyViewOrThrowable - Any object or null; however, Activity, View and Throwable may generate additional datasource.
        optionalData - Map or null. This data takes precedence over customData and globalCustomData.
        eventName - preferably Tealium.EVENT_NAME_LINK or Tealium.EVENT_NAME_VIEW. this will determine the Tealium utag method call syntax. This parameter allows you to associate an Activity with a link event and View with a view event, contrary to the default behavior.
        Returns:
        true if the event was queued or dispatched, false if it was suppressed or there was other complications. See LogCat for details.

      • getStatus

        public static Tealium.Status getStatus()

      • map

        public static java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> map(java.lang.String... keyValuePairs)
        Converts a list of Strings into a Map by interpreting the String list as key-value pairs. In the event of an empty-set or odd number of keys, an empty Map is returned (so as to be fault resistant). If the Tealium.OPTION_SILENCE_ERRORS wasn't included in initialization LogCat will report the Exception.
        Parameters:
        keyValuePairs - strings inserted into the map as key, value, key, value...
        Returns:
        the constructed map if successful, empty map otherwise. Usage: Tealium.track("key0", "value0", "key1", "value1"..."keyN", "valueN");

      • setAccelerationSensitivity

        public static boolean setAccelerationSensitivity(float sensitivity)
        Utilized by mobile companion to determine what constitutes a "shake" to determine its launch. Some devices will fire off 10 shake events for another's single event. This may be useful for only allowing certain devices to launch mobile companion, or minimizing premature/unexpected launches. In the event Tealium is not initialized, the error will be printed in LogCat (if not suppressed by the OPTION_SILENCE_ERRORS flag). In the event an inappropriate sensitivity given (any value less than or equal to 0) the default sensitivity will be set and the warning printed in LogCat (if not suppressed by the OPTION_SILENCE_WARNINGS flag).
        Parameters:
        sensitivity - - Some value greater than 0. The magnitude of the value correlates to the amount of acceleration it takes to register a "shake event".
        Returns:
        boolean - true if there were no issues setting the value.

      • getLastDispatch

        public static JSONObject getLastDispatch()
        Returns:
        the last tracked event that was either sent out or queued.
